It is definitely, 100%, better at story and character writing. It's not even close, actually. The average Ragnarok side quest is infinitely more interesting and engaging than any main mission in FW.

>but technically HFW is astronomically better, it being still playable on the ps4 and still be so fucking gorgeous is ashtonishing
Ragnarok is also perfectly playable on the PS4, looking fucking gorgeous.

>GOWR still looks the same as it did with the 2018 game, technically it was the same game, but HFW was on another level.
That applies even more to FW. There's absolutely nothing about FW, design-wise, that an Assassin's Creed game from 5 years ago wasn't already doing. Ragnarok didn't reinvent the wheel but it excels at what it proposes in a way that FW simply doesn't. Ragnarok revisits some locations from the 2018 game but they're not only a small portion of it, they always serve the storytelling, which is the focus of the game. Also, there's much more to a game's visuals than pretty colors and cool costumes. Ragnarok is beautifully designed too but it edges FW in how it technically implements its visual elements, like overall quality of character animations and fidelity of motion capture performances. It's why it swept the technical categories even while losing Game of the Year.
